name: Hubble's newest camera images ghostly star-forming pillar of gas and dust
description:
This picture, taken by the newly installed Advanced Camera for Surveys (ACS) aboard the NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope, shows the upper 2.5 light-years of the Cone, a height that equals 23 million roundtrips to the Moon.

Name:	Cone Nebula, NGC 2264
Type:	Milky Way : Nebula
Distance:	3000 light years
Constellation:	Monoceros
Category:	Nebulae

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.

Credit: ESA/Hubble/NASA
